The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Thursday, March 31, 2005

 Roads to avoid

 BB Ganguly Street, Lalbazar Street and Ganesh Chandra Avenue. Youth Congress Lalbazar Chalo agitation from Raja Subodh Mullick Square at noon.

 Lecture

 Prof Sukanta Chaudhuri will speak on ?The Handkerchief and the Cat?, as part of The Harendralal Basak Lecture Series in English Literature, at Botany Lecture Theatre, Presidency College, 4.30 pm.

 Dance

 A Bharatanatyam duet by Sutapa Awon Pradhan and Umesh Bheemanna Madesh, presented by Nrityalok, at Gyan Mancha, 6.30 pm. Guru V.P. Dhananjayan will be felicitated on the occasion.

 Screening

 A special screening of Journey with Jyoti Basu, directed by Goutam Ghose, at Nandan I, 6.30 pm.

 The Confirmation Candidate, At the Record Shop, A Disastrous Violin Solo and The Inheritance will be screened, as part of a retrospective on Karl Valentin, at Max Mueller Bhavan, 6.30 pm.

 Exhibition

 An expo of handlooms of West Bengal, Orissa, Bihar and Jharkhand at Rangmanch, Swabhumi, 2 pm to 8 pm.

 Art watch

 Tradition in Modernity, an exhibition of works of five contemporary artists, at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.




